rything from conferences to publications, the book explains the steps for creating a concise and communicative graphic to highlight the most important aspects of research—and to clarify researchers’ own thinking. The resulting book is an essential element of any scientist’s, engineer’s, or designer’s library.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGraphic artsvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aVisual communication in sciencevHandbooks, manuals, etc. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226829173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226829173/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles